│ to ptr))`, confirms that the `alloca` `%a` was replaced by a constant pointer. The      │
│ backtrace points to the `VerifierPass` running after `ipsccp`, which strongly indicates │
│ that `ipsccp` generated the malformed IR.                                               │
│                                                                                         │
│ ### 3. Root Cause Analysis                                                              │
│                                                                                         │
│ The root cause lies within the `SCCPInstVisitor::visitTerminator` function in           │
│ `llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/SCCPSolver.cpp`. This function is responsible for            │
│ propagating information along control flow edges. When it encounters a conditional      │
│ branch based on an `icmp` instruction, it calls `getPredicateInfoFor` to deduce facts   │
│ about values in the successor blocks.                                                   │
│                                                                                         │
│ The problem is in how `getPredicateInfoFor` (and the logic it relies on) handles        │
│ comparisons between an `AllocaInst` and a `Constant`. It fails to recognize that an     │
│ `alloca` cannot be equal to a non-null constant pointer (unless that pointer originates │
│ from specific intrinsics like `@llvm.stacksave`, which is not the case here). Instead   │
│ of concluding that the `icmp eq` is always false, the pass proceeds as if the equality  │
│ is possible. This leads to the incorrect propagation of the constant value to the       │
│ `alloca` along the true edge of the branch.                                             │
│                                                                                         │
│ The fix is to explicitly teach `getPredicateInfoFor` that a comparison `icmp eq         │
│ <alloca>, <const>` is always false if the constant is not a null pointer. This will     │
│ cause the true branch to be marked as unreachable, preventing the incorrect             │
